t al. 2009; Ichimura et al. 2015a; Ichimura et al. 2015b). Increased activation of estrogen receptor alpha, or estrogenicity, is generally studied in mammalian cell lines in vitro (U.S. EPA, 2022) and rarely confirmed in laboratory mammal studies in vivo. &nbsp;Gene knock-out studies have been useful in essentiality of ERa and kisspeptin genes in the hypothalamus- pituitary-gonadal (HPG) axis, with subsequent hormone addition restoring normal function (d&#39;Anglemont de Tassigny et al. 2007; Clarkson et al. 2008; Dubois et al. 2015). &nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 16:19:41 +0000 2026"}